.TH "i915_set_dma_info" 9 "i915_set_dma_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i915_set_dma_info \- set all relevant PCI dma info as configured for the platform
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i915_set_dma_info
.BI "(struct drm_i915_private *i915 "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "i915" 12
valid i915 instance
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the dma max segment size, device and coherent masks.  The dma mask set
needs to occur before i915_ggtt_probe_hw.

A couple of platforms have special needs.  Address them as well.
